properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: An intense low pressure system is tracking across Vancouver Island. Strong winds will affect coastal B.C. tonight until early Saturday morning. Western sections of Vancouver Island from Zeballos to Sooke and southern sections of Victoria are currently under a wind warning. The low is forecast to track across Vancouver Island tonight and into Washington State by early Saturday morning. Ahead of the low, strong southeast winds up to 70 km/h can be expected over northern sections of East Vancouver Island and Sunshine Coast. Strong southwest winds of 50 to 70 km/h will affect the Southern Gulf Islands, East Vancouver Island, Inland Vancouver Island, and over southern sections of Metro Vancouver and western Fraser Valley beginning this evening. Behind the low, strong northwest winds up to 70 km/h are expected to sweep through the Strait of Georgia and may affect western sections of Metro Vancouver near the Strait of Georgia. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
